A warm and enjoyable bastion of "old school" River North pubs, holding out against the onslaught of trendy and MUCH more expensive bars and restaurants in the area.  You won't find foie gras or a 12-deep list of curated cocktails here.  But you will find great pub food (with an Irish flair!), a well stocked bar (manned by friendly, knowledgeable bartenders), and an excellent beer selection (ranging from local micro to national "macro" breweries).  There is a reason this place has lasted as long as it has.

A classic Chicago Irish bar, and a cornerstone of the Gallery District in River North. More than a bar, I often recommend it as a valid lunch or casual dinner location. They have a surprising menu, and the food is consistently remarkable for its quality. The options extend way beyong typical pub grub and requisite burgers, and include a wide range of sandwiches, wraps, huge salads, and dinners, many of which exhibiting Irish tendencies, including the Shepherds Pie and Guinness Stew. Order Pulled Pork with a Snakebite.

Brehon hasn't been a good bar in years. I work at a restaurant down the street and use to go in to Brehon a lot with several others after our shifts. The quality of service rapidly declined about three years ago, which resulted in us taking our patronage somewhere else. Final returned to Brehon last night for a co-workers birthday celebration. About 10 of us arrived  around midnight and went to the back bar. The place was not busy for a Saturday night in River north. It was hot and muggy inside. They had removed their pool table, leaving the back area emptier looking than usual. It took ten minutes for a bartender to acknowledge us. Even when she finally greeted us, she acted as if we were an inconvenience. They were out of the beer we ordered, so we chose another. After ordering a few pitchers and shots, I asked if they still had an industry discount like in the past. These discounts are important to kitchen staff because most of us are underpaid but still enjoy our booze. She was very annoyed that I asked and informed me that we were 'not on the list' and 'had to be regulars to get discounts'. She then proceeded to over charge for shots, ringing them as 'up'. After the initial transaction, she never came back to serve us. We were the only group in the back bar area and thus completely ignored. I refused to spend another dime after being treated the way we were. But the people still ordering drinks were forced to go around to the front bar to do so. We did nothing to deserve this horrendously rude level of service. This experience only reaffirmed why I stopped going to Brehon pub. I will never go back. I am frequently asked for bar recommendations in the area by guests at the restaurant.  Brehon will never be on that list, just as I am not on theirs.
